article.description: Long Island U. 69, Cent. Connecticut St. 65
article.headline: Long Island U. 69, Cent. Connecticut St. 65
article.linkText: Long Island U. 69, Cent. Connecticut St. 65
article.story: NEW YORK -- Jaytornah Wisseh scored 20 points, including two free throws with 5 seconds left, as Long Island University held off Central Connecticut State on Saturday. The Blackbirds (4-3, 2-0 Northeast Conference) led 61-48 with 6:14 remaining, but the Blue Devils (2-4, 1-1) whittled it to 65-63 with 24 seconds left. LIU's Kyle Johnson made two free throws with 19 seconds to go for a 67-63 lead, but Joe Seymore's jumper made it a two-point game with 6 seconds left. Wisseh was quickly fouled by Devan Bailey and made both shots. After trailing by nine in the second half, the Blue Devils got within 45-42 before a 10-0 run over a span of 3:21 put LIU ahead 55-42. Michael Culpo, who scored 15 points off the bench, had a pair of 3-pointers in that run. Seymore and David Simmons led Central Connecticut State with 15 points each.
